textDelta: which fat soluble vitamin reduces cardiovascular disease? There is no one fat soluble vitamin that has a specific impact on reducing cardiovascular disease. However, taking a variety of fat soluble vitamins can help reduce the risk of heart disease.

which fat soluble vitamin reduces cardiovascular disease when used in a diet? Some fat soluble vitamins that may reduce cardiovascular disease risk when used in a diet are vitamin E, beta-carotene, and vitamin C.

What were the 'open-door notes'? The 'open-door notes' were a series of notes written by the president of the United States in the wake of the September 11th terrorist attacks. The notes were released on September 12th, 2001, one day after the terrorist attacks. The notes were intended to show the American people that the United States was working closely with its international partners to investigate and prevent future terrorist attacks.
